The paper discusses the training of auto-encoders, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on the trade-off between reconstruction error and compression, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of denoising and contractive properties, which are related to information theory (cs.IT).
